title 0.5 Single Page Application

browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/spa
server-->browser: HTML-code
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/main.css
server-->browser: main.css
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/spa.js
server-->browser: spa.js

note over browser:
js code requests data.json from the server
end note

browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/data.json
server-->browser: [{ content: "HTML is easy", date: "2019-05-23" }, ...]

note over browser:
browser executes the event handler
that renders notes to display
end note

note over browerser:
user enters a note and clicks the save button
js code takes the note (and date) and pushes it to the already existing notes object
js code redraws the notes on the browser to match
js code makes POST request to add the new note to the server

browser->server: HTTP POST https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/new_note_spa
server-->browser: [{"message": "note created"}]
